metadata.name: Rakaposhi
metadata.description:
Rakaposhi is a mountain in the Karakorum range in Pakistan. It is ranked 27th highest in the world and 12th highest in Pakistan with an altitude of 7788 meters above sea level. It is more popular for it's beauty than it's rank. Rakaposhi means "Shining Wall" in local language. It was first climbed in 1958 by British climbers.

This image was taken during motorbike tour to "Khunjerab Pass" in 2021 located on the northern border of Pakistan with China.it is the highest border crossing in the world.

Edition : 1/1
Dimensions : 4000x6000
Collection : Incredible Pakistan
